usdAddressPoolMIB.name: usdAddressPoolMIB

revisions.description: Added usdAddressPoolProfileTable to support an address pool with multiple address ranges.
Added pool exhaustion variables and notifications for high pool utilization and pool exhaustion.
Initial version of this MIB module.

usdAddressPoolMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Road Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 E-mail: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdAddressPoolMIB.description: The Address Pool MIB for the Unisphere Networks enterprise.

usdAddressPoolTable.name: usdAddressPoolTable
usdAddressPoolTable.description: A table of IP address pool configuration entries.

usdAddressPoolEntry.name: usdAddressPoolEntry
usdAddressPoolEntry.description: An entry describing an IP address pool configuration.

usdAddressPoolIndex.name: usdAddressPoolIndex
usdAddressPoolIndex.description: An arbitrary integer index that distinguishes this address pool.

usdAddressPoolRowStatus.name: usdAddressPoolRowStatus
usdAddressPoolRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of address pools. Only value 'active' will be observed with GET. Only values 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' are supported for SET. Once created, entry content cannot be modified except by deleting and recreating an entry with the same index.

usdAddressPoolName.name: usdAddressPoolName
usdAddressPoolName.description: The name of this address pool. Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII graphics character set (codes 32 through 126).

usdAddressPoolStart.name: usdAddressPoolStart
usdAddressPoolStart.description: The starting IP address for the range of addresses comprising this pool.

usdAddressPoolEnd.name: usdAddressPoolEnd
usdAddressPoolEnd.description: The ending IP address for the range of addresses comprising this pool.

usdAddressPoolSize.name: usdAddressPoolSize
usdAddressPoolSize.description: The number of addresses available in this pool.

usdAddressPoolInUse.name: usdAddressPoolInUse
usdAddressPoolInUse.description: The number of addresses currently allocated from this pool.

usdAddressPoolHighUtilThreshold.name: usdAddressPoolHighUtilThreshold
usdAddressPoolHighUtilThreshold.description: The value of address pool utilization, where if reached for the first time, will generate a high address pool utilization event to the management entity on this system. The value of this object must be greater than the value of usdAddressPoolAbatedUtilThreshold.

usdAddressPoolAbatedUtilThreshold.name: usdAddressPoolAbatedUtilThreshold
usdAddressPoolAbatedUtilThreshold.description: The value of address pool utilization that is used to determine when to generate an abated address pool utilization event notification to the management entity on this system. The value of this object must be less than the value of the usdAddressPoolHighUtilThreshold. The abated address pool utilization event is sent once if the high address pool utilization threshold is reached and utilization falls to the value of this object.

usdAddressPoolUtilPct.name: usdAddressPoolUtilPct
usdAddressPoolUtilPct.description: The current address utilization for this pool.

usdAddressPoolTrapEnable.name: usdAddressPoolTrapEnable
usdAddressPoolTrapEnable.description: The configuration setting for address pool notifications. Setting this object to enable(1) will enable the sending of usdAddressPool event notifications to the management entity on this device. Setting this object to false(2) will disable event notification reports.

usdAddressPoolProfileTable.name: usdAddressPoolProfileTable
usdAddressPoolProfileTable.description: A table of IP address pool profile entries.

usdAddressPoolProfileEntry.name: usdAddressPoolProfileEntry
usdAddressPoolProfileEntry.description: An IP address pool profile entry.

usdAddressPoolProfileIndex.name: usdAddressPoolProfileIndex
usdAddressPoolProfileIndex.description: A monotonically increasing integer for the sole purpose of indexing entries within the named address pool.

usdAddressPoolProfileRowStatus.name: usdAddressPoolProfileRowStatus
usdAddressPoolProfileRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of address pools. Only value 'active' will be observed with GET. Only values 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' are supported for SET. Once created, entry content cannot be modified except by deleting and recreating an entry with the same index.

usdAddressPoolProfileStart.name: usdAddressPoolProfileStart
usdAddressPoolProfileStart.description: The starting IP address for the range of addresses comprising this pool.

usdAddressPoolProfileEnd.name: usdAddressPoolProfileEnd
usdAddressPoolProfileEnd.description: The ending IP address for the range of addresses comprising this pool.

usdAddressPoolProfileSize.name: usdAddressPoolProfileSize
usdAddressPoolProfileSize.description: The number of addresses available in this pool.

usdAddressPoolProfileInUse.name: usdAddressPoolProfileInUse
usdAddressPoolProfileInUse.description: The number of addresses currently allocated from this pool.

usdAddressPoolNextPoolIndex.name: usdAddressPoolNextPoolIndex
usdAddressPoolNextPoolIndex.description: Coordinate usdAddressPoolIndex value allocation for entries in usdAddressPoolTable. A GET of this object returns the next available usdAddressPoolIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated usdAddressPoolTable; or zero, if no valid usdAddressPoolIndex is available. This object returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that a new index allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

usdAddressPoolHighAddrUtil.name: usdAddressPoolHighAddrUtil
usdAddressPoolHighAddrUtil.description: Reports address pool utilization has reached the configured high utilization threshold.

usdAddressPoolAbatedAddrUtil.name: usdAddressPoolAbatedAddrUtil
usdAddressPoolAbatedAddrUtil.description: Reports address pool utilization has fallen to the configured abated threshold level.

usdAddressPoolNoAddresses.name: usdAddressPoolNoAddresses
usdAddressPoolNoAddresses.description: Reports address pool has exhausted its supply of addresses. This trap is issued every time a request is made to allocate an address from a fully utilized pool.

usdAddressPoolCompliance.name: usdAddressPoolCompliance
usdAddressPoolCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems providing local address pools. This statement became obsolete when pool exhaustion variables and notifications were added.

usdAddressPoolCompliance2.name: usdAddressPoolCompliance2
usdAddressPoolCompliance2.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems providing local address pools. This statement became obsolete when support was added for address pools with multiple address ranges.

usdAddressPoolCompliance3.name: usdAddressPoolCompliance3
usdAddressPoolCompliance3.description: The compliance statement for systems providing local address pools.

usdAddressPoolGroup.name: usdAddressPoolGroup
usdAddressPoolGroup.description: Obsolete collection of objects providing management of local address pools. This group became obsolete when pool exhaustion variables and notifications were added.

usdAddressPoolGroup2.name: usdAddressPoolGroup2
usdAddressPoolGroup2.description: The basic collection of objects providing management of local address pools. This group was deprecated when support was added for address pools with multiple address ranges.

usdAddressPoolTrapGroup.name: usdAddressPoolTrapGroup
usdAddressPoolTrapGroup.description: The notifications providing alarms for high pool utilization and pool exhaustion of local address pools.

usdAddressPoolGroup3.name: usdAddressPoolGroup3
usdAddressPoolGroup3.description: The basic collection of objects providing management of local address pools.
